##Shanghai Aid Hubei Medical Team: If we can't cure pneumonia, we won't care

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Li Jiawei is a reporter for the paper

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Yu-fei, cartography

On the first day in Wuhan, the Shanghai Medical Team knew that it was not only the patient's body that needed to be cured, but also that discharge from the hospital would not be the end of service.

And so far, they've done a pretty good job.

On February 7, the 4th medical team of Shanghai Zhongshan Hospital was stationed in the East Hospital of Wuhan University People's Hospital. Two wards (20 and 22 wards with 80 beds) were taken over under the new system. All the patients were in serious and critical condition.

As of February 21, just two weeks to fully cure, more than 70 patients with severe illness has been more than 30 people into mild illness, the number of nearly half.

The silence of an 87-year-old conservatory professor

Just arrived in Wuhan when the scene, the medical team member, digestive Doctor Li Feng remembers clearly.

The two wards they went to, which had been converted from cardiology wards to ICU, were set up with the necessary medical facilities and placed in different categories. The management process of medical treatment, nursing and medication in each area of the ward has been reconstructed.

Head nurse Pan Wenyan has more than 20 years of intensive care experience, she knows a simple truth, "rescue, the doctor said to intubate, the nurse must be able to take out the needed things at any time, can not have a minute delay. ".

Conditions in the wards have improved, but the condition of the patients has worried the staff.

There was an 87-year-old gentleman, always lying in a hospital bed in silence. Every time Li Feng went into the ward, he saw the food handed out to him intact on the table.

The old man, a former professor of the conservatory, had been hospitalized for more than 40 days with new pneumonia. He doesn't talk much, and sometimes he doesn't ring the nurse after a saline drip.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the intensive care unit of the East Hospital of Wuhan University People's Hospital, a nurse from the Shanghai medical team fed porridge to an 87-year-old man. All images in this article are provided by the interviewees

This is not an isolated case. Many intensive care units in Wuhan have similar worrying situation, they are mostly elderly, common family cluster infection, in the hospital lost heart, worry and missing family members.

"When we went in to ask 'how are you? ' They all looked at US rather indifferently, " he said. A patient told the doctor, in addition to their own, her husband and daughter have been sick in the hospital, only the son-in-law and grandson is still outside isolation. She's worried about them.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the intensive care unit of the East Hospital of Wuhan University People's Hospital, Shanghai medical staff communicated with patients in the ward.

One Instruction: Talk to each patient

Li Feng to their understanding of the situation the first time to reflect up, other doctors and nurses also have relevant reports. Immediately, the Shanghai Medical Team issued a directive: Medical staff to protect their own absolute security, while ward rounds as much as possible to stay in the ward for a while, to talk to every patient, especially the elderly patients.

At the same time, oranges, apples, and other nutrients were distributed to each patient by health care workers. Some patients'relatives for various reasons can not care for them, the medical team to come forward, they should be equipped with supplies.

These things aren't expensive, but the patients are happy when they get them. The doctors and nurses also felt the warmth of the cold ward.

One day, Li Feng and medical team leader Luo Zhe went down to rounds, walked to the aforementioned 87-year-old gentleman bed. Luo Zhe asked him the last two days is not good, whether the body is not comfortable.

"I want to go home" was all the old man said, but when he said it, both doctors sensed the implication -- that she was going to give up.

Luo Zhe did not answer the old gentleman's request directly, but asked: "Old sir, you originally in the band is not the conductor? "

The old man looked up and his eyes lit up. "No, I'm not a conductor. I play instruments. I blow them. "

"You're in no condition to play your instrument now, " he continued, seeing the old man's spirits rising. "When you're better, go back and play. "

A simple conversation, the old man relaxed.

After that, every time the doctors and nurses entered the ward, they chatted with the old man for a while about his family's latest situation. He gradually opened up to the doctors and nurses. They kept the doctors and nurses informed of any reactions and any discomfort in the treatment, the doctor adjusted the treatment plan according to the situation in time. His children were concerned about their father, calling him often, and the doctor promptly informed the family of his illness.

The old man is getting better and better these days. He began to eat voluntarily, eating fruits and supplements. In Clinic, the condition of acute breath and Hypoxia had been improved obviously. On a more positive note, chest CT and blood work show that his condition is improving across the board.

"We can't say we're done with pneumonia. "

So far, there is no specific drug for NCP. The core of Shanghai medical team is multidisciplinary comprehensive treatment. From the experience of the healer, it is very important to increase autoimmunity, which is closely related to the patient's mood and Diet.

After many days of running-in, between the medical care more and more handy, medical care, nursing has done more comprehensive.

A critically ill patient was delirious, the doctor had to arrange a daily high flow of oxygen, and the nurse regularly changed the patient's diaper, wiped his body, and rolled over. The doctor also inserted a gastric tube and injected the patient with nutrients.

"curing a patient is not just medical treatment, it is all-round support, " Li said.

Each patient is evaluated every 5 days or so. Doctors observe whether symptoms such as chest tightness and shortness of breath have improved. Chest CT and blood tests are performed to analyze imaging findings and determine whether inflammation has been absorbed. At the same time, patients appetite, sleep situation is also the focus of attention. A patient plan. After each treatment, doctors gather to review their experiences and look for improvements in subsequent cases.

Now the two wards, there have been more than 30 severe patients have been turned into mild illness, some patients will be cured and discharged. However, the medical team's services do not stop there.

We have a 75-year-old patient with new coronary pneumonia with renal function problems. Throughout his treatment, the Shanghai medical team contacted the local hospital in Wuhan and asked the doctor to enter the ward to perform regular hemodialysis for the patient to ensure his kidney function.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At the East Hospital of Wuhan University People's Hospital, Zhongshan Hospital medical team part of the nurses on duty group photo.

At present, the patient's new coronary pneumonia has been basically cured, will soon be discharged from hospital. Given that he is on dialysis twice a week, medical teams are contacting hospitals to prepare him for post-discharge treatment.

"We are contacting the local hospital to help the patient get stable dialysis after discharge, " Li said. "We can't say that we don't care about curing pneumonia. "
